<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 4:53AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Armstrong and northeastern Randall Counties through 530 AM CDT...
At 453 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake Tanglewood, or 9 miles northeast of Canyon, moving east at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Lake Tanglewood and Timbercreek Canyon.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
